  "text": "Clearly, EF equals (1-RF). All points (e.g. P1 and P2) on a line (here c1) with the same angle (phi) carry identical values for EF. However, EF cannot be used to interpret the working point unless a second piece of information is explicitly known, e.g. ESV, EDV or stroke volume (SV) [CITATION_1] . If it is desired to not include any of these traditional variables, then the hypotenuse emerges as an easily recognized EF companion (EFC) candidate. For mathematical derivation and calculation of the hypotenuse EFC, see Supplement Fig. S1 .",
